CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 27, 1954, pg. A10, reads: "They Danced the 'Can-Can' - When the annual Sweetheart Ball was held at the Centre Avenue YMCA last Saturday, Victor Hereford and a group of dancers from the studio were on hand to provide some of the entertainment during the intermission from dancing. This group danced the 'Can Can.' Left to right: Miss Yvonne Thompkins [Jones not Thompkins], Miss Juanita Baskin, Victor Hereford, Delores Stewart and Mamie Hamilton. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dancers in can can costumes Yvonne Jones (Kemp), Juanita Baskin, Victor Hereford, Delores Stewart, and Mamie Hamilton posed lifting skirts in Centre Avenue YMCA for Sweetheart Ball
